page.title: 03ECOLOGY
page.content: {Ecology { The woodland in the area we covered was populated with many animals of different kinds. Priory copse was the most densley populated area for animals. It had many birds of different species, the most common being rooks, crows and blackbirds. I also saw the remains of an egg from a large bird. To go with the birds there were many butterflies. One that I saw was a Meadow-Brown butterfly. In the middle of the copse I found deer tracks and deer feeders. There is also an area in the copse purely for pheasant raising. There are also some rabbit warrens. All the copse is covered with trees of different kinds such as the Beech, Fir, Oak, and Pine
